                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7353</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hostetter</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Hermosillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-21T16:00:00-07:23">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s February 19, 6 p.m. In response to wire to General Serrano who is
                    conducting campaign against the Yaquis, says that as result of the campaign
                    against the Yaquis the valley is at present perfectly safe, settlers having
                    ample protection. Claims the campaign is being vigorously pushed; has sufficient
                    troops to protect that region.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hostetter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
